title: Places to study at the University of Minnesota
name: Places to study at the University of Minnesota

properties.name: Coffman Memorial Union
properties.description: This is a great place to eat and have a study break.

properties.name: Mathematics Library
properties.description: If you're in a math class, this library is great for doing homework related to the subject.

properties.name: Walter Library
properties.description: This is a great place to study. It has a cafe, computer labs, and group study rooms.

properties.name: Washington Avenue to Pleasant Street SE
properties.description: This is one route you could take from Wilson Library to Walter Library, and vice versa.

properties.name: Wilson Library
properties.description: This is another great place to study, with many computer labs and private study rooms.
